Detailed Description

For setting up connections between two Bluetooth Devices link keys are necessary. These link keys are used for authentication and encryption. When a BtDevicePairRequest is executed successfully, these link keys where created and stored for later use when for expample the paired remote device tries to reconnect to the local device.
When no pairing is done, every time a remote device tries to connect to the local device, depending on the security settings of the requested profile, a request for a pin number is executed. This can be suppressed by pairing devices together.
When a untrusted pairing is established and a paired remote device tries to connect to a profile requiring authorization the local device asks its owner for confirmation of the requested connection. So a pairing request has a parameter to the the Bluetooth Stack to create a either a trusted or untrusted pairing.

Member Function Documentation

BOOLEAN BtDevicePairRequest::Execute (   )  [protected, virtual]
 

Sumbit this request to the Bluetooth Stack.

Execute instructs this request to send itself to the Bluetooth Stack for execution purposes.
In the base class of all Bluetooth Requests - BtRequest - there is an interface defined, that all requests must fullfill respectively implement. Some functions in this interface are declared pure virtual because they can not be implemented in the base classes. Execute is one of these functions.Because the execution of various requests differ very strong, the implmentation of this function is done by the various concrete request classes.

Returns:
TRUE: The setup of the stack parameters was successfull and the Bluetooth stack accepted the requested operation.
FALSE: Either the setup of the stack parameters failed or the Bluetooth stack rejected the requested operation.

Implements BtRequest.

BOOLEAN BtDevicePairRequest::GetCreateTrust (   )  const
 

Does this request create a trusted pairing or not?

GetCreateTrust returns whether this request creates a trusted or untrusted pairing when it is executed by the Bluetooth Stack.

Returns:
TRUE: The pairing should be created as trusted.
FALSE: The pairing should be created as untrusted.

BtRequestType BtDevicePairRequest::GetRequestType (   )  const [virtual]
 

Get type of this request.

The runtime type information feature is not supported by all compilers which this framework is used with. So a rudimentary type information system is implemnted by this class. Each type of request that has no subtypes (leaf class) must return an unique type identifier. GetRequestType returns this type idenifier which is implemented as an enumeration type.

Returns:
A BtRequestType containing the type that describes this request.

Implements BtRequest.

BOOLEAN BtDevicePairRequest::OnMessage (  const Message &  message  )  [protected, virtual]
 

Message dispatching member function.

The OnMessage member function is the first entry point in every dispatcher for the reception of messages. From there on it will be routed to the appropriate On... member function, if it should be handled by this dispatcher or passed back to the superior dispatcher.

Returns:
TRUE: The received message has be handle. No further handling for the message is needed.
FALSE: The received message is not handled by this dispatcher. Route it forward to the next dispatcher.

Implements BtLocalRequest.

Register the required messages for receipt.
